93uint32_t ConvertIceTransportTypeToCandidateFilter(
94 PeerConnectionInterface::IceTransportsType type) {
95 switch (type) {
96 case PeerConnectionInterface::kNone:
97 return cricket::CF_NONE;
98 case PeerConnectionInterface::kRelay:
99 return cricket::CF_RELAY;
100 case PeerConnectionInterface::kNoHost:
101 return (cricket::CF_ALL & ~cricket::CF_HOST);
102 case PeerConnectionInterface::kAll:
103 return cricket::CF_ALL;
104 default:
105 RTC_NOTREACHED();
106 }
107 return cricket::CF_NONE;
108}

110IceCandidatePairType GetIceCandidatePairCounter(
111 const cricket::Candidate& local,
112 const cricket::Candidate& remote) {
113 const auto& l = local.type();
114 const auto& r = remote.type();
115 const auto& host = LOCAL_PORT_TYPE;
116 const auto& srflx = STUN_PORT_TYPE;
117 const auto& relay = RELAY_PORT_TYPE;
118 const auto& prflx = PRFLX_PORT_TYPE;
119 if (l == host && r == host) {
120 bool local_hostname =
121 !local.address().hostname().empty() && local.address().IsUnresolvedIP();
122 bool remote_hostname = !remote.address().hostname().empty() &&
123 remote.address().IsUnresolvedIP();
124 bool local_private = IPIsPrivate(local.address().ipaddr());
125 bool remote_private = IPIsPrivate(remote.address().ipaddr());
126 if (local_hostname) {
127 if (remote_hostname) {
128 return kIceCandidatePairHostNameHostName;
129 } else if (remote_private) {
130 return kIceCandidatePairHostNameHostPrivate;
131 } else {
132 return kIceCandidatePairHostNameHostPublic;
133 }
134 } else if (local_private) {
135 if (remote_hostname) {
136 return kIceCandidatePairHostPrivateHostName;
137 } else if (remote_private) {
138 return kIceCandidatePairHostPrivateHostPrivate;
139 } else {
140 return kIceCandidatePairHostPrivateHostPublic;
141 }
142 } else {
143 if (remote_hostname) {
144 return kIceCandidatePairHostPublicHostName;
145 } else if (remote_private) {
146 return kIceCandidatePairHostPublicHostPrivate;
147 } else {
148 return kIceCandidatePairHostPublicHostPublic;
149 }
150 }
151 }
152 if (l == host && r == srflx)
153 return kIceCandidatePairHostSrflx;
154 if (l == host && r == relay)
155 return kIceCandidatePairHostRelay;
156 if (l == host && r == prflx)
157 return kIceCandidatePairHostPrflx;
158 if (l == srflx && r == host)
159 return kIceCandidatePairSrflxHost;
160 if (l == srflx && r == srflx)
161 return kIceCandidatePairSrflxSrflx;
162 if (l == srflx && r == relay)
163 return kIceCandidatePairSrflxRelay;
164 if (l == srflx && r == prflx)
165 return kIceCandidatePairSrflxPrflx;
166 if (l == relay && r == host)
167 return kIceCandidatePairRelayHost;
168 if (l == relay && r == srflx)
169 return kIceCandidatePairRelaySrflx;
170 if (l == relay && r == relay)
171 return kIceCandidatePairRelayRelay;
172 if (l == relay && r == prflx)
173 return kIceCandidatePairRelayPrflx;
174 if (l == prflx && r == host)
175 return kIceCandidatePairPrflxHost;
176 if (l == prflx && r == srflx)
177 return kIceCandidatePairPrflxSrflx;
178 if (l == prflx && r == relay)
179 return kIceCandidatePairPrflxRelay;
180 return kIceCandidatePairMax;
181}

183absl::optional<int> RTCConfigurationToIceConfigOptionalInt(
184 int rtc_configuration_parameter) {
185 if (rtc_configuration_parameter ==
186 webrtc::PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration::kUndefined) {
187 return absl::nullopt;
188 }
189 return rtc_configuration_parameter;
190}

192// Check if the changes of IceTransportsType motives an ice restart.
193bool NeedIceRestart(bool surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed,
194 PeerConnectionInterface::IceTransportsType current,
195 PeerConnectionInterface::IceTransportsType modified) {
196 if (current == modified) {
197 return false;
198 }
199
200 if (!surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed) {
201 return true;
202 }
203
204 auto current_filter = ConvertIceTransportTypeToCandidateFilter(current);
205 auto modified_filter = ConvertIceTransportTypeToCandidateFilter(modified);
206
207 // If surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed is true and we
208 // extend the filter, then no ice restart is needed.
209 return (current_filter & modified_filter) != current_filter;
210}

212cricket::IceConfig ParseIceConfig(
213 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration& config) {
214 cricket::ContinualGatheringPolicy gathering_policy;
215 switch (config.continual_gathering_policy) {
216 case PeerConnectionInterface::GATHER_ONCE:
217 gathering_policy = cricket::GATHER_ONCE;
218 break;
219 case PeerConnectionInterface::GATHER_CONTINUALLY:
220 gathering_policy = cricket::GATHER_CONTINUALLY;
221 break;
222 default:
223 RTC_NOTREACHED();
224 gathering_policy = cricket::GATHER_ONCE;
225 }
226
227 cricket::IceConfig ice_config;
228 ice_config.receiving_timeout = RTCConfigurationToIceConfigOptionalInt(
229 config.ice_connection_receiving_timeout);
230 ice_config.prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs =
231 config.prioritize_most_likely_ice_candidate_pairs;
232 ice_config.backup_connection_ping_interval =
233 RTCConfigurationToIceConfigOptionalInt(
234 config.ice_backup_candidate_pair_ping_interval);
235 ice_config.continual_gathering_policy = gathering_policy;
236 ice_config.presume_writable_when_fully_relayed =
237 config.presume_writable_when_fully_relayed;
238 ice_config.surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed =
239 config.surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed;
240 ice_config.ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity =
241 config.ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity;
242 ice_config.ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity =
243 config.ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity;
244 ice_config.ice_check_min_interval = config.ice_check_min_interval;
245 ice_config.ice_unwritable_timeout = config.ice_unwritable_timeout;
246 ice_config.ice_unwritable_min_checks = config.ice_unwritable_min_checks;
247 ice_config.ice_inactive_timeout = config.ice_inactive_timeout;
248 ice_config.stun_keepalive_interval = config.stun_candidate_keepalive_interval;
249 ice_config.network_preference = config.network_preference;
250 ice_config.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval =
251 config.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_ms;
252 return ice_config;
253}

255// Ensures the configuration doesn't have any parameters with invalid values,
256// or values that conflict with other parameters.
257//
258// Returns RTCError::OK() if there are no issues.
259RTCError ValidateConfiguration(
260 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration& config) {
261 return cricket::P2PTransportChannel::ValidateIceConfig(
262 ParseIceConfig(config));
263}

269bool DtlsEnabled(const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration& configuration,
270 const PeerConnectionFactoryInterface::Options& options,
271 const PeerConnectionDependencies& dependencies) {
272 if (options.disable_encryption)
273 return false;
274
275 // Enable DTLS by default if we have an identity store or a certificate.
276 bool default_enabled =
277 (dependencies.cert_generator || !configuration.certificates.empty());
278
279 // The |configuration| can override the default value.
280 return configuration.enable_dtls_srtp.value_or(default_enabled);
281}

408RTCErrorOr<rtc::scoped_refptr<PeerConnection>> PeerConnection::Create(
409 rtc::scoped_refptr<ConnectionContext> context,
410 const PeerConnectionFactoryInterface::Options& options,
411 std::unique_ptr<RtcEventLog> event_log,
412 std::unique_ptr<Call> call,
413 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration& configuration,
414 PeerConnectionDependencies dependencies) {
415 RTCError config_error = cricket::P2PTransportChannel::ValidateIceConfig(
416 ParseIceConfig(configuration));
417 if (!config_error.ok()) {
418 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Invalid ICE configuration: "
419 << config_error.message();
420 return config_error;
421 }
422
423 if (!dependencies.allocator) {
424 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
425 << "PeerConnection initialized without a PortAllocator? "
426 "This shouldn't happen if using PeerConnectionFactory.";
427 return RTCError(
428 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
429 "Attempt to create a PeerConnection without a PortAllocatorFactory");
430 }
431
432 if (!dependencies.observer) {
433 // TODO(deadbeef): Why do we do this?
434 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "PeerConnection initialized without a "
435 "PeerConnectionObserver";
436 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
437 "Attempt to create a PeerConnection without an observer");
438 }
439
440 bool is_unified_plan =
441 configuration.sdp_semantics == SdpSemantics::kUnifiedPlan;
442 bool dtls_enabled = DtlsEnabled(configuration, options, dependencies);
443
444 // Interim code: If an AsyncResolverFactory is given, but not an
445 // AsyncDnsResolverFactory, wrap it in a WrappingAsyncDnsResolverFactory
446 // If neither is given, create a WrappingAsyncDnsResolverFactory wrapping
447 // a BasicAsyncResolver.
448 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/12598): Remove code once all callers pass a
449 // AsyncDnsResolverFactory.
450 if (dependencies.async_dns_resolver_factory &&
451 dependencies.async_resolver_factory) {
452 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
453 << "Attempt to set both old and new type of DNS resolver factory";
454 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
455 "Both old and new type of DNS resolver given");
456 }
457 if (dependencies.async_resolver_factory) {
458 dependencies.async_dns_resolver_factory =
459 std::make_unique<WrappingAsyncDnsResolverFactory>(
460 std::move(dependencies.async_resolver_factory));
461 } else {
462 dependencies.async_dns_resolver_factory =
463 std::make_unique<WrappingAsyncDnsResolverFactory>(
464 std::make_unique<BasicAsyncResolverFactory>());
465 }
466
467 // The PeerConnection constructor consumes some, but not all, dependencies.
468 auto pc = rtc::make_ref_counted<PeerConnection>(
469 context, options, is_unified_plan, std::move(event_log), std::move(call),
470 dependencies, dtls_enabled);
471 RTCError init_error = pc->Initialize(configuration, std::move(dependencies));
472 if (!init_error.ok()) {
473 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "PeerConnection initialization failed";
474 return init_error;
475 }
476 return pc;
477}
478
479PeerConnection::PeerConnection(
480 rtc::scoped_refptr<ConnectionContext> context,
481 const PeerConnectionFactoryInterface::Options& options,
482 bool is_unified_plan,
483 std::unique_ptr<RtcEventLog> event_log,
484 std::unique_ptr<Call> call,
485 PeerConnectionDependencies& dependencies,
486 bool dtls_enabled)
487 : context_(context),
488 options_(options),
489 observer_(dependencies.observer),
490 is_unified_plan_(is_unified_plan),
491 event_log_(std::move(event_log)),
492 event_log_ptr_(event_log_.get()),
493 async_dns_resolver_factory_(
494 std::move(dependencies.async_dns_resolver_factory)),
495 port_allocator_(std::move(dependencies.allocator)),
496 ice_transport_factory_(std::move(dependencies.ice_transport_factory)),
497 tls_cert_verifier_(std::move(dependencies.tls_cert_verifier)),
498 call_(std::move(call)),
499 call_ptr_(call_.get()),
500 // RFC 3264: The numeric value of the session id and version in the
501 // o line MUST be representable with a "64 bit signed integer".
502 // Due to this constraint session id |session_id_| is max limited to
503 // LLONG_MAX.
504 session_id_(rtc::ToString(rtc::CreateRandomId64() & LLONG_MAX)),
505 dtls_enabled_(dtls_enabled),
506 data_channel_controller_(this),
507 message_handler_(signaling_thread()),
508 weak_factory_(this) {
509 worker_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this] {
510 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
511 worker_thread_safety_ = PendingTaskSafetyFlag::Create();
512 if (!call_)
513 worker_thread_safety_->SetNotAlive();
514 });
515}
516
517PeerConnection::~PeerConnection() {
518 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::~PeerConnection");
519 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
520
521 if (sdp_handler_) {
522 sdp_handler_->PrepareForShutdown();
523 }
524
525 // Need to stop transceivers before destroying the stats collector because
526 // AudioRtpSender has a reference to the StatsCollector it will update when
527 // stopping.
528 if (rtp_manager()) {
529 for (const auto& transceiver : rtp_manager()->transceivers()->List()) {
530 transceiver->StopInternal();
531 }
532 }
533
534 stats_.reset(nullptr);
535 if (stats_collector_) {
536 stats_collector_->WaitForPendingRequest();
537 stats_collector_ = nullptr;
538 }
539
540 if (sdp_handler_) {
541 // Don't destroy BaseChannels until after stats has been cleaned up so that
542 // the last stats request can still read from the channels.
543 sdp_handler_->DestroyAllChannels();
544
545 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Session: " << session_id() << " is destroyed.";
546
547 sdp_handler_->ResetSessionDescFactory();
548 }
549
550 // port_allocator_ and transport_controller_ live on the network thread and
551 // should be destroyed there.
552 network_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this] {
553 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
554 TeardownDataChannelTransport_n();
555 transport_controller_.reset();
556 port_allocator_.reset();
557 if (network_thread_safety_)
558 network_thread_safety_->SetNotAlive();
559 });
560
561 // call_ and event_log_ must be destroyed on the worker thread.
562 worker_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this] {
563 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
564 worker_thread_safety_->SetNotAlive();
565 call_.reset();
566 // The event log must outlive call (and any other object that uses it).
567 event_log_.reset();
568 });
569}

571RTCError PeerConnection::Initialize(
572 const PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration& configuration,
573 PeerConnectionDependencies dependencies) {
574 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
575 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::Initialize");
576
577 cricket::ServerAddresses stun_servers;
578 std::vector<cricket::RelayServerConfig> turn_servers;
579
580 RTCErrorType parse_error =
581 ParseIceServers(configuration.servers, &stun_servers, &turn_servers);
582 if (parse_error != RTCErrorType::NONE) {
583 return RTCError(parse_error, "ICE server parse failed");
584 }
585
586 // Add the turn logging id to all turn servers
587 for (cricket::RelayServerConfig& turn_server : turn_servers) {
588 turn_server.turn_logging_id = configuration.turn_logging_id;
589 }
590
591 // Note if STUN or TURN servers were supplied.
592 if (!stun_servers.empty()) {
593 NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::STUN_SERVER_ADDED);
594 }
595 if (!turn_servers.empty()) {
596 NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::TURN_SERVER_ADDED);
597 }
598
599 // Network thread initialization.
600 network_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this, &stun_servers,
601 &turn_servers, &configuration,
602 &dependencies] {
603 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
604 network_thread_safety_ = PendingTaskSafetyFlag::Create();
605 InitializePortAllocatorResult pa_result =
606 InitializePortAllocator_n(stun_servers, turn_servers, configuration);
607 // Send information about IPv4/IPv6 status.
608 PeerConnectionAddressFamilyCounter address_family =
609 pa_result.enable_ipv6 ? kPeerConnection_IPv6 : kPeerConnection_IPv4;
610 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.IPMetrics", address_family,
611 kPeerConnectionAddressFamilyCounter_Max);
612 InitializeTransportController_n(configuration, dependencies);
613 });
614
615 configuration_ = configuration;
616
617 stats_ = std::make_unique<StatsCollector>(this);
618 stats_collector_ = RTCStatsCollector::Create(this);
619
620 sdp_handler_ =
621 SdpOfferAnswerHandler::Create(this, configuration, dependencies);
622
623 rtp_manager_ = std::make_unique<RtpTransmissionManager>(
624 IsUnifiedPlan(), signaling_thread(), worker_thread(), channel_manager(),
625 &usage_pattern_, observer_, stats_.get(), [this]() {
626 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
627 sdp_handler_->UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
628 });
629
630 // Add default audio/video transceivers for Plan B SDP.
631 if (!IsUnifiedPlan()) {
632 rtp_manager()->transceivers()->Add(
633 RtpTransceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpTransceiver>::Create(
634 signaling_thread(),
635 new RtpTransceiver(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO, channel_manager())));
636 rtp_manager()->transceivers()->Add(
637 RtpTransceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpTransceiver>::Create(
638 signaling_thread(),
639 new RtpTransceiver(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO, channel_manager())));
640 }
641
642 int delay_ms = configuration.report_usage_pattern_delay_ms
643 ? *configuration.report_usage_pattern_delay_ms
644 : REPORT_USAGE_PATTERN_DELAY_MS;
645 message_handler_.RequestUsagePatternReport(
646 [this]() {
647 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
648 ReportUsagePattern();
649 },
650 delay_ms);
651
652 return RTCError::OK();
653}
654
655void PeerConnection::InitializeTransportController_n(
656 const RTCConfiguration& configuration,
657 const PeerConnectionDependencies& dependencies) {
658 JsepTransportController::Config config;
659 config.redetermine_role_on_ice_restart =
660 configuration.redetermine_role_on_ice_restart;
661 config.ssl_max_version = options_.ssl_max_version;
662 config.disable_encryption = options_.disable_encryption;
663 config.bundle_policy = configuration.bundle_policy;
664 config.rtcp_mux_policy = configuration.rtcp_mux_policy;
665 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/9891) - Remove options_.crypto_options then remove
666 // this stub.
667 config.crypto_options = configuration.crypto_options.has_value()
668 ? *configuration.crypto_options
669 : options_.crypto_options;
670 config.transport_observer = this;
671 config.rtcp_handler = InitializeRtcpCallback();
672 config.event_log = event_log_ptr_;
673#if defined(ENABLE_EXTERNAL_AUTH)
674 config.enable_external_auth = true;
675#endif
676 config.active_reset_srtp_params = configuration.active_reset_srtp_params;
677
678 // DTLS has to be enabled to use SCTP.
679 if (dtls_enabled_) {
680 config.sctp_factory = context_->sctp_transport_factory();
681 }
682
683 config.ice_transport_factory = ice_transport_factory_.get();
684 config.on_dtls_handshake_error_ =
685 [weak_ptr = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr()](rtc::SSLHandshakeError s) {
686#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
687 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(
688 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.DtlsHandshakeError", static_cast<int>(s),
689 static_cast<int>(rtc::SSLHandshakeError::MAX_VALUE));
690#else
691 // FIXME: weak_ptr check is unsafe since destruction happens in signaling thread while the callback is called in networking thread.
692 if (weak_ptr) {
693 weak_ptr->OnTransportControllerDtlsHandshakeError(s);
694 }
695#endif
696 };
697
698 transport_controller_.reset(
699 new JsepTransportController(network_thread(), port_allocator_.get(),
700 async_dns_resolver_factory_.get(), config));
701
702 transport_controller_->SubscribeIceConnectionState(
703 [this](cricket::IceConnectionState s) {
704 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
705 if (s == cricket::kIceConnectionConnected) {
706 ReportTransportStats();
707 }
708 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
709 ToQueuedTask(signaling_thread_safety_.flag(), [this, s]() {
710 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
711 OnTransportControllerConnectionState(s);
712 }));
713 });
714 transport_controller_->SubscribeConnectionState(
715 [this](PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState s) {
716 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
717 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
718 ToQueuedTask(signaling_thread_safety_.flag(), [this, s]() {
719 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
720 SetConnectionState(s);
721 }));
722 });
723 transport_controller_->SubscribeStandardizedIceConnectionState(
724 [this](PeerConnectionInterface::IceConnectionState s) {
725 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
726 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
727 ToQueuedTask(signaling_thread_safety_.flag(), [this, s]() {
728 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
729 SetStandardizedIceConnectionState(s);
730 }));
731 });
732 transport_controller_->SubscribeIceGatheringState(
733 [this](cricket::IceGatheringState s) {
734 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
735 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
736 ToQueuedTask(signaling_thread_safety_.flag(), [this, s]() {
737 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
738 OnTransportControllerGatheringState(s);
739 }));
740 });
741 transport_controller_->SubscribeIceCandidateGathered(
742 [this](const std::string& transport,
743 const std::vector<cricket::Candidate>& candidates) {
744 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
745 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
746 ToQueuedTask(signaling_thread_safety_.flag(),
747 [this, t = transport, c = candidates]() {
748 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
749 OnTransportControllerCandidatesGathered(t, c);
750 }));
751 });
752 transport_controller_->SubscribeIceCandidateError(
753 [this](const cricket::IceCandidateErrorEvent& event) {
754 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
755 signaling_thread()->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
756 signaling_thread_safety_.flag(), [this, event = event]() {
757 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
758 OnTransportControllerCandidateError(event);
759 }));
760 });
761 transport_controller_->SubscribeIceCandidatesRemoved(
762 [this](const std::vector<cricket::Candidate>& c) {
763 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
764 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
765 ToQueuedTask(signaling_thread_safety_.flag(), [this, c = c]() {
766 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
767 OnTransportControllerCandidatesRemoved(c);
768 }));
769 });
770 transport_controller_->SubscribeIceCandidatePairChanged(
771 [this](const cricket::CandidatePairChangeEvent& event) {
772 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
773 signaling_thread()->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
774 signaling_thread_safety_.flag(), [this, event = event]() {
775 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
776 OnTransportControllerCandidateChanged(event);
777 }));
778 });
779
780 transport_controller_->SetIceConfig(ParseIceConfig(configuration));
781}

816RTCErrorOr<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInterface>> PeerConnection::AddTrack(
817 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamTrackInterface> track,
818 const std::vector<std::string>& stream_ids) {
819 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
820 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::AddTrack");
821 if (!track) {
822 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER, "Track is null.");
823 }
824 if (!(track->kind() == MediaStreamTrackInterface::kAudioKind ||
825 track->kind() == MediaStreamTrackInterface::kVideoKind)) {
826 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
827 "Track has invalid kind: " + track->kind());
828 }
829 if (IsClosed()) {
830 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
831 "PeerConnection is closed.");
832 }
833 if (rtp_manager()->FindSenderForTrack(track)) {
834 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
835 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
836 "Sender already exists for track " + track->id() + ".");
837 }
838 auto sender_or_error = rtp_manager()->AddTrack(track, stream_ids);
839 if (sender_or_error.ok()) {
840 sdp_handler_->UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
841 stats_->AddTrack(track);
842 }
843 return sender_or_error;
844}

846bool PeerConnection::RemoveTrack(RtpSenderInterface* sender) {
847 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::RemoveTrack");
848 return RemoveTrackNew(sender).ok();
849}
850
851RTCError PeerConnection::RemoveTrackNew(
852 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInterface> sender) {
853 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
854 if (!sender) {
855 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER, "Sender is null.");
856 }
857 if (IsClosed()) {
858 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
859 "PeerConnection is closed.");
860 }
861 if (IsUnifiedPlan()) {
862 auto transceiver = FindTransceiverBySender(sender);
863 if (!transceiver || !sender->track()) {
864 return RTCError::OK();
865 }
866 sender->SetTrack(nullptr);
867 if (transceiver->direction() == RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv) {
868 transceiver->internal()->set_direction(
869 RtpTransceiverDirection::kRecvOnly);
870 } else if (transceiver->direction() == RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendOnly) {
871 transceiver->internal()->set_direction(
872 RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive);
873 }
874 } else {
875 bool removed;
876 if (sender->media_type() == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
877 removed = rtp_manager()->GetAudioTransceiver()->internal()->RemoveSender(
878 sender);
879 } else {
880 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO, sender->media_type());
881 removed = rtp_manager()->GetVideoTransceiver()->internal()->RemoveSender(
882 sender);
883 }
884 if (!removed) {
885 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
886 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
887 "Couldn't find sender " + sender->id() + " to remove.");
888 }
889 }
890 sdp_handler_->UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
891 return RTCError::OK();
892}

956
957RTCErrorOr<rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverInterface>>
958PeerConnection::AddTransceiver(
959 cricket::MediaType media_type,
960 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamTrackInterface> track,
961 const RtpTransceiverInit& init,
962 bool update_negotiation_needed) {
963 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
964 RTC_DCHECK((media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
965 media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO));
966 if (track) {
967 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media_type,
968 (track->kind() == MediaStreamTrackInterface::kAudioKind
969 ? cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO
970 : cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO));
971 }
972
973 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR(kSimulcastNumberOfEncodings,
974 init.send_encodings.size(), 0, 7, 8);
975
976 size_t num_rids = absl::c_count_if(init.send_encodings,
977 [](const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding) {
978 return !encoding.rid.empty();
979 });
980 if (num_rids > 0 && num_rids != init.send_encodings.size()) {
981 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
982 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
983 "RIDs must be provided for either all or none of the send encodings.");
984 }
985
986 if (num_rids > 0 && absl::c_any_of(init.send_encodings,
987 [](const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding) {
988 return !IsLegalRsidName(encoding.rid);
989 })) {
990 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
991 "Invalid RID value provided.");
992 }
993
994 if (absl::c_any_of(init.send_encodings,
995 [](const RtpEncodingParameters& encoding) {
996 return encoding.ssrc.has_value();
997 })) {
998 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
999 RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER,
1000 "Attempted to set an unimplemented parameter of RtpParameters.");
1001 }
1002
1003 RtpParameters parameters;
1004 parameters.encodings = init.send_encodings;
1005
1006 // Encodings are dropped from the tail if too many are provided.
1007 size_t max_simulcast_streams =
1008 media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ? kMaxSimulcastStreams : 1u;
1009 if (parameters.encodings.size() > max_simulcast_streams) {
1010 parameters.encodings.erase(
1011 parameters.encodings.begin() + max_simulcast_streams,
1012 parameters.encodings.end());
1013 }
1014
1015 // Single RID should be removed.
1016 if (parameters.encodings.size() == 1 &&
1017 !parameters.encodings[0].rid.empty()) {
1018 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Removing RID: " << parameters.encodings[0].rid << ".";
1019 parameters.encodings[0].rid.clear();
1020 }
1021
1022 // If RIDs were not provided, they are generated for simulcast scenario.
1023 if (parameters.encodings.size() > 1 && num_rids == 0) {
1024 rtc::UniqueStringGenerator rid_generator;
1025 for (RtpEncodingParameters& encoding : parameters.encodings) {
1026 encoding.rid = rid_generator();
1027 }
1028 }
1029
1030 if (UnimplementedRtpParameterHasValue(parameters)) {
1031 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
1032 RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER,
1033 "Attempted to set an unimplemented parameter of RtpParameters.");
1034 }
1035
1036 auto result = cricket::CheckRtpParametersValues(parameters);
1037 if (!result.ok()) {
1038 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(result.type(), result.message());
1039 }
1040
1041 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Adding " << cricket::MediaTypeToString(media_type)
1042 << " transceiver in response to a call to AddTransceiver.";
1043 // Set the sender ID equal to the track ID if the track is specified unless
1044 // that sender ID is already in use.
1045 std::string sender_id = (track && !rtp_manager()->FindSenderById(track->id())
1046 ? track->id()
1047 : rtc::CreateRandomUuid());
1048 auto sender = rtp_manager()->CreateSender(
1049 media_type, sender_id, track, init.stream_ids, parameters.encodings);
1050 auto receiver =
1051 rtp_manager()->CreateReceiver(media_type, rtc::CreateRandomUuid());
1052 auto transceiver = rtp_manager()->CreateAndAddTransceiver(sender, receiver);
1053 transceiver->internal()->set_direction(init.direction);
1054
1055 if (update_negotiation_needed) {
1056 sdp_handler_->UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
1057 }
1058
1059 return rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpTransceiverInterface>(transceiver);
1060}
1061
1062void PeerConnection::OnNegotiationNeeded() {
1063 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1064 RTC_DCHECK(!IsClosed());
1065 sdp_handler_->UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
1066}
1067
1068rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInterface> PeerConnection::CreateSender(
1069 const std::string& kind,
1070 const std::string& stream_id) {
1071 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1072 RTC_CHECK(!IsUnifiedPlan()) << "CreateSender is not available with Unified "
1073 "Plan SdpSemantics. Please use AddTransceiver "
1074 "instead.";
1075 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::CreateSender");
1076 if (IsClosed()) {
1077 return nullptr;
1078 }
1079
1080 // Internally we need to have one stream with Plan B semantics, so we
1081 // generate a random stream ID if not specified.
1082 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids;
1083 if (stream_id.empty()) {
1084 stream_ids.push_back(rtc::CreateRandomUuid());
1085 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
1086 << "No stream_id specified for sender. Generated stream ID: "
1087 << stream_ids[0];
1088 } else {
1089 stream_ids.push_back(stream_id);
1090 }
1091
1092 // TODO(steveanton): Move construction of the RtpSenders to RtpTransceiver.
1093 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderProxyWithInternal<RtpSenderInternal>> new_sender;
1094 if (kind == MediaStreamTrackInterface::kAudioKind) {
1095 auto audio_sender = AudioRtpSender::Create(
1096 worker_thread(), rtc::CreateRandomUuid(), stats_.get(), rtp_manager());
1097 audio_sender->SetMediaChannel(rtp_manager()->voice_media_channel());
1098 new_sender = RtpSenderProxyWithInternal<RtpSenderInternal>::Create(
1099 signaling_thread(), audio_sender);
1100 rtp_manager()->GetAudioTransceiver()->internal()->AddSender(new_sender);
1101 } else if (kind == MediaStreamTrackInterface::kVideoKind) {
1102 auto video_sender = VideoRtpSender::Create(
1103 worker_thread(), rtc::CreateRandomUuid(), rtp_manager());
1104 video_sender->SetMediaChannel(rtp_manager()->video_media_channel());
1105 new_sender = RtpSenderProxyWithInternal<RtpSenderInternal>::Create(
1106 signaling_thread(), video_sender);
1107 rtp_manager()->GetVideoTransceiver()->internal()->AddSender(new_sender);
1108 } else {
1109 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "CreateSender called with invalid kind: " << kind;
1110 return nullptr;
1111 }
1112 new_sender->internal()->set_stream_ids(stream_ids);
1113
1114 return new_sender;
1115}

1148
1149bool PeerConnection::GetStats(StatsObserver* observer,
1150 MediaStreamTrackInterface* track,
1151 StatsOutputLevel level) {
1152 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::GetStats");
1153 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1154 if (!observer) {
1155 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "GetStats - observer is NULL.";
1156 return false;
1157 }
1158
1159 RTC_LOG_THREAD_BLOCK_COUNT();
1160
1161 stats_->UpdateStats(level);
1162 // The StatsCollector is used to tell if a track is valid because it may
1163 // remember tracks that the PeerConnection previously removed.
1164 if (track && !stats_->IsValidTrack(track->id())) {
1165 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "GetStats is called with an invalid track: "
1166 << track->id();
1167 return false;
1168 }
1169 message_handler_.PostGetStats(observer, stats_.get(), track);
1170
1171 return true;
1172}
1173
1174void PeerConnection::GetStats(RTCStatsCollectorCallback* callback) {
1175 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::GetStats");
1176 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1177 RTC_DCHECK(stats_collector_);
1178 RTC_DCHECK(callback);
1179 RTC_LOG_THREAD_BLOCK_COUNT();
1180 stats_collector_->GetStatsReport(callback);
1181}
1182
1183void PeerConnection::GetStats(
1184 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInterface> selector,
1185 rtc::scoped_refptr<RTCStatsCollectorCallback> callback) {
1186 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::GetStats");
1187 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1188 RTC_DCHECK(callback);
1189 RTC_DCHECK(stats_collector_);
1190 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderInternal> internal_sender;
1191 if (selector) {
1192 for (const auto& proxy_transceiver :
1193 rtp_manager()->transceivers()->List()) {
1194 for (const auto& proxy_sender :
1195 proxy_transceiver->internal()->senders()) {
1196 if (proxy_sender == selector) {
1197 internal_sender = proxy_sender->internal();
1198 break;
1199 }
1200 }
1201 if (internal_sender)
1202 break;
1203 }
1204 }
1205 // If there is no |internal_sender| then |selector| is either null or does not
1206 // belong to the PeerConnection (in Plan B, senders can be removed from the
1207 // PeerConnection). This means that "all the stats objects representing the
1208 // selector" is an empty set. Invoking GetStatsReport() with a null selector
1209 // produces an empty stats report.
1210 stats_collector_->GetStatsReport(internal_sender, callback);
1211}
1212
1213void PeerConnection::GetStats(
1214 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInterface> selector,
1215 rtc::scoped_refptr<RTCStatsCollectorCallback> callback) {
1216 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::GetStats");
1217 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1218 RTC_DCHECK(callback);
1219 RTC_DCHECK(stats_collector_);
1220 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverInternal> internal_receiver;
1221 if (selector) {
1222 for (const auto& proxy_transceiver :
1223 rtp_manager()->transceivers()->List()) {
1224 for (const auto& proxy_receiver :
1225 proxy_transceiver->internal()->receivers()) {
1226 if (proxy_receiver == selector) {
1227 internal_receiver = proxy_receiver->internal();
1228 break;
1229 }
1230 }
1231 if (internal_receiver)
1232 break;
1233 }
1234 }
1235 // If there is no |internal_receiver| then |selector| is either null or does
1236 // not belong to the PeerConnection (in Plan B, receivers can be removed from
1237 // the PeerConnection). This means that "all the stats objects representing
1238 // the selector" is an empty set. Invoking GetStatsReport() with a null
1239 // selector produces an empty stats report.
1240 stats_collector_->GetStatsReport(internal_receiver, callback);
1241}

1272absl::optional<bool> PeerConnection::can_trickle_ice_candidates() {
1273 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1274 const SessionDescriptionInterface* description = current_remote_description();
1275 if (!description) {
1276 description = pending_remote_description();
1277 }
1278 if (!description) {
1279 return absl::nullopt;
1280 }
1281 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/7443): Change to retrieve from session-level option.
1282 if (description->description()->transport_infos().size() < 1) {
1283 return absl::nullopt;
1284 }
1285 return description->description()->transport_infos()[0].description.HasOption(
1286 "trickle");
1287}

1289rtc::scoped_refptr<DataChannelInterface> PeerConnection::CreateDataChannel(
1290 const std::string& label,
1291 const DataChannelInit* config) {
1292 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1293 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::CreateDataChannel");
1294
1295 bool first_datachannel = !data_channel_controller_.HasDataChannels();
1296
1297 std::unique_ptr<InternalDataChannelInit> internal_config;
1298 if (config) {
1299 internal_config.reset(new InternalDataChannelInit(*config));
1300 }
1301 rtc::scoped_refptr<DataChannelInterface> channel(
1302 data_channel_controller_.InternalCreateDataChannelWithProxy(
1303 label, internal_config.get()));
1304 if (!channel.get()) {
1305 return nullptr;
1306 }
1307
1308 // Trigger the onRenegotiationNeeded event for
1309 // the first SCTP DataChannel.
1310 if (first_datachannel) {
1311 sdp_handler_->UpdateNegotiationNeeded();
1312 }
1313 NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::DATA_ADDED);
1314 return channel;
1315}

1374PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration PeerConnection::GetConfiguration() {
1375 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1376 return configuration_;
1377}
1378
1379RTCError PeerConnection::SetConfiguration(
1380 const RTCConfiguration& configuration) {
1381 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1382 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::SetConfiguration");
1383 if (IsClosed()) {
1384 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
1385 "SetConfiguration: PeerConnection is closed.");
1386 }
1387
1388 // According to JSEP, after setLocalDescription, changing the candidate pool
1389 // size is not allowed, and changing the set of ICE servers will not result
1390 // in new candidates being gathered.
1391 if (local_description() && configuration.ice_candidate_pool_size !=
1392 configuration_.ice_candidate_pool_size) {
1393 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
1394 "Can't change candidate pool size after calling "
1395 "SetLocalDescription.");
1396 }
1397
1398 if (local_description() &&
1399 configuration.crypto_options != configuration_.crypto_options) {
1400 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
1401 "Can't change crypto_options after calling "
1402 "SetLocalDescription.");
1403 }
1404
1405 // The simplest (and most future-compatible) way to tell if the config was
1406 // modified in an invalid way is to copy each property we do support
1407 // modifying, then use operator==. There are far more properties we don't
1408 // support modifying than those we do, and more could be added.
1409 RTCConfiguration modified_config = configuration_;
1410 modified_config.servers = configuration.servers;
1411 modified_config.type = configuration.type;
1412 modified_config.ice_candidate_pool_size =
1413 configuration.ice_candidate_pool_size;
1414 modified_config.prune_turn_ports = configuration.prune_turn_ports;
1415 modified_config.turn_port_prune_policy = configuration.turn_port_prune_policy;
1416 modified_config.surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed =
1417 configuration.surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed;
1418 modified_config.ice_check_min_interval = configuration.ice_check_min_interval;
1419 modified_config.ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity =
1420 configuration.ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity;
1421 modified_config.ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity =
1422 configuration.ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity;
1423 modified_config.ice_unwritable_timeout = configuration.ice_unwritable_timeout;
1424 modified_config.ice_unwritable_min_checks =
1425 configuration.ice_unwritable_min_checks;
1426 modified_config.ice_inactive_timeout = configuration.ice_inactive_timeout;
1427 modified_config.stun_candidate_keepalive_interval =
1428 configuration.stun_candidate_keepalive_interval;
1429 modified_config.turn_customizer = configuration.turn_customizer;
1430 modified_config.network_preference = configuration.network_preference;
1431 modified_config.active_reset_srtp_params =
1432 configuration.active_reset_srtp_params;
1433 modified_config.turn_logging_id = configuration.turn_logging_id;
1434 modified_config.allow_codec_switching = configuration.allow_codec_switching;
1435 modified_config.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_ms =
1436 configuration.stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_ms;
1437 if (configuration != modified_config) {
1438 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
1439 "Modifying the configuration in an unsupported way.");
1440 }
1441
1442 // Validate the modified configuration.
1443 RTCError validate_error = ValidateConfiguration(modified_config);
1444 if (!validate_error.ok()) {
1445 return validate_error;
1446 }
1447
1448 // Note that this isn't possible through chromium, since it's an unsigned
1449 // short in WebIDL.
1450 if (configuration.ice_candidate_pool_size < 0 ||
1451 configuration.ice_candidate_pool_size > static_cast<int>(UINT16_MAX)) {
1452 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_RANGE);
1453 }
1454
1455 // Parse ICE servers before hopping to network thread.
1456 cricket::ServerAddresses stun_servers;
1457 std::vector<cricket::RelayServerConfig> turn_servers;
1458 RTCErrorType parse_error =
1459 ParseIceServers(configuration.servers, &stun_servers, &turn_servers);
1460 if (parse_error != RTCErrorType::NONE) {
1461 return RTCError(parse_error);
1462 }
1463 // Add the turn logging id to all turn servers
1464 for (cricket::RelayServerConfig& turn_server : turn_servers) {
1465 turn_server.turn_logging_id = configuration.turn_logging_id;
1466 }
1467
1468 // Note if STUN or TURN servers were supplied.
1469 if (!stun_servers.empty()) {
1470 NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::STUN_SERVER_ADDED);
1471 }
1472 if (!turn_servers.empty()) {
1473 NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::TURN_SERVER_ADDED);
1474 }
1475
1476 const bool has_local_description = local_description() != nullptr;
1477
1478 const bool needs_ice_restart =
1479 modified_config.servers != configuration_.servers ||
1480 NeedIceRestart(
1481 configuration_.surface_ice_candidates_on_ice_transport_type_changed,
1482 configuration_.type, modified_config.type) ||
1483 modified_config.GetTurnPortPrunePolicy() !=
1484 configuration_.GetTurnPortPrunePolicy();
1485 cricket::IceConfig ice_config = ParseIceConfig(modified_config);
1486
1487 // Apply part of the configuration on the network thread. In theory this
1488 // shouldn't fail.
1489 if (!network_thread()->Invoke<bool>(
1490 RTC_FROM_HERE,
1491 [this, needs_ice_restart, &ice_config, &stun_servers, &turn_servers,
1492 &modified_config, has_local_description] {
1493 // As described in JSEP, calling setConfiguration with new ICE
1494 // servers or candidate policy must set a "needs-ice-restart" bit so
1495 // that the next offer triggers an ICE restart which will pick up
1496 // the changes.
1497 if (needs_ice_restart)
1498 transport_controller_->SetNeedsIceRestartFlag();
1499
1500 transport_controller_->SetIceConfig(ice_config);
1501 return ReconfigurePortAllocator_n(
1502 stun_servers, turn_servers, modified_config.type,
1503 modified_config.ice_candidate_pool_size,
1504 modified_config.GetTurnPortPrunePolicy(),
1505 modified_config.turn_customizer,
1506 modified_config.stun_candidate_keepalive_interval,
1507 has_local_description);
1508 })) {
1509 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INTERNAL_ERROR,
1510 "Failed to apply configuration to PortAllocator.");
1511 }
1512
1513 if (configuration_.active_reset_srtp_params !=
1514 modified_config.active_reset_srtp_params) {
1515 // TODO(tommi): move to the network thread - this hides an invoke.
1516 transport_controller_->SetActiveResetSrtpParams(
1517 modified_config.active_reset_srtp_params);
1518 }
1519
1520 if (modified_config.allow_codec_switching.has_value()) {
1521 std::vector<cricket::VideoMediaChannel*> channels;
1522 for (const auto& transceiver : rtp_manager()->transceivers()->List()) {
1523 if (transceiver->media_type() != cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
1524 continue;
1525
1526 auto* video_channel = static_cast<cricket::VideoChannel*>(
1527 transceiver->internal()->channel());
1528 if (video_channel)
1529 channels.push_back(video_channel->media_channel());
1530 }
1531
1532 worker_thread()->Invoke<void>(
1533 RTC_FROM_HERE,
1534 [channels = std::move(channels),
1535 allow_codec_switching = *modified_config.allow_codec_switching]() {
1536 for (auto* ch : channels)
1537 ch->SetVideoCodecSwitchingEnabled(allow_codec_switching);
1538 });
1539 }
1540
1541 configuration_ = modified_config;
1542 return RTCError::OK();
1543}

1565RTCError PeerConnection::SetBitrate(const BitrateSettings& bitrate) {
1566 if (!worker_thread()->IsCurrent()) {
1567 return worker_thread()->Invoke<RTCError>(
1568 RTC_FROM_HERE, [&]() { return SetBitrate(bitrate); });
1569 }
1570 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
1571
1572 const bool has_min = bitrate.min_bitrate_bps.has_value();
1573 const bool has_start = bitrate.start_bitrate_bps.has_value();
1574 const bool has_max = bitrate.max_bitrate_bps.has_value();
1575 if (has_min && *bitrate.min_bitrate_bps < 0) {
1576 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
1577 "min_bitrate_bps <= 0");
1578 }
1579 if (has_start) {
1580 if (has_min && *bitrate.start_bitrate_bps < *bitrate.min_bitrate_bps) {
1581 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
1582 "start_bitrate_bps < min_bitrate_bps");
1583 } else if (*bitrate.start_bitrate_bps < 0) {
1584 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
1585 "curent_bitrate_bps < 0");
1586 }
1587 }
1588 if (has_max) {
1589 if (has_start && *bitrate.max_bitrate_bps < *bitrate.start_bitrate_bps) {
1590 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
1591 "max_bitrate_bps < start_bitrate_bps");
1592 } else if (has_min && *bitrate.max_bitrate_bps < *bitrate.min_bitrate_bps) {
1593 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
1594 "max_bitrate_bps < min_bitrate_bps");
1595 } else if (*bitrate.max_bitrate_bps < 0) {
1596 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
1597 "max_bitrate_bps < 0");
1598 }
1599 }
1600
1601 RTC_DCHECK(call_.get());
1602 call_->SetClientBitratePreferences(bitrate);
1603
1604 return RTCError::OK();
1605}

1721
1722void PeerConnection::Close() {
1723 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1724 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "PeerConnection::Close");
1725
1726 RTC_LOG_THREAD_BLOCK_COUNT();
1727
1728 if (IsClosed()) {
1729 return;
1730 }
1731 // Update stats here so that we have the most recent stats for tracks and
1732 // streams before the channels are closed.
1733 stats_->UpdateStats(kStatsOutputLevelStandard);
1734
1735 ice_connection_state_ = PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionClosed;
1736 Observer()->OnIceConnectionChange(ice_connection_state_);
1737 standardized_ice_connection_state_ =
1738 PeerConnectionInterface::IceConnectionState::kIceConnectionClosed;
1739 connection_state_ = PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState::kClosed;
1740 Observer()->OnConnectionChange(connection_state_);
1741
1742 sdp_handler_->Close();
1743
1744 NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::CLOSE_CALLED);
1745
1746 for (const auto& transceiver : rtp_manager()->transceivers()->List()) {
1747 transceiver->internal()->SetPeerConnectionClosed();
1748 if (!transceiver->stopped())
1749 transceiver->StopInternal();
1750 }
1751
1752 // Ensure that all asynchronous stats requests are completed before destroying
1753 // the transport controller below.
1754 if (stats_collector_) {
1755 stats_collector_->WaitForPendingRequest();
1756 }
1757
1758 // Don't destroy BaseChannels until after stats has been cleaned up so that
1759 // the last stats request can still read from the channels.
1760 sdp_handler_->DestroyAllChannels();
1761
1762 // The event log is used in the transport controller, which must be outlived
1763 // by the former. CreateOffer by the peer connection is implemented
1764 // asynchronously and if the peer connection is closed without resetting the
1765 // WebRTC session description factory, the session description factory would
1766 // call the transport controller.
1767 sdp_handler_->ResetSessionDescFactory();
1768 rtp_manager_->Close();
1769
1770 network_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this] {
1771 // Data channels will already have been unset via the DestroyAllChannels()
1772 // call above, which triggers a call to TeardownDataChannelTransport_n().
1773 // TODO(tommi): ^^ That's not exactly optimal since this is yet another
1774 // blocking hop to the network thread during Close(). Further still, the
1775 // voice/video/data channels will be cleared on the worker thread.
1776 transport_controller_.reset();
1777 port_allocator_->DiscardCandidatePool();
1778 if (network_thread_safety_) {
1779 network_thread_safety_->SetNotAlive();
1780 }
1781 });
1782
1783 worker_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [this] {
1784 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
1785 worker_thread_safety_->SetNotAlive();
1786 call_.reset();
1787 // The event log must outlive call (and any other object that uses it).
1788 event_log_.reset();
1789 });
1790 ReportUsagePattern();
1791 // The .h file says that observer can be discarded after close() returns.
1792 // Make sure this is true.
1793 observer_ = nullptr;
1794
1795 // Signal shutdown to the sdp handler. This invalidates weak pointers for
1796 // internal pending callbacks.
1797 sdp_handler_->PrepareForShutdown();
1798}
1799
1800void PeerConnection::SetIceConnectionState(IceConnectionState new_state) {
1801 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
1802 if (ice_connection_state_ == new_state) {
1803 return;
1804 }
1805
1806 // After transitioning to "closed", ignore any additional states from
1807 // TransportController (such as "disconnected").
1808 if (IsClosed()) {
1809 return;
1810 }
1811
1812 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing IceConnectionState " << ice_connection_state_
1813 << " => " << new_state;
1814 RTC_DCHECK(ice_connection_state_ !=
1815 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionClosed);
1816
1817 ice_connection_state_ = new_state;
1818 Observer()->OnIceConnectionChange(ice_connection_state_);
1819}
1820
1821void PeerConnection::SetStandardizedIceConnectionState(
1822 PeerConnectionInterface::IceConnectionState new_state) {
1823 if (standardized_ice_connection_state_ == new_state) {
1824 return;
1825 }
1826
1827 if (IsClosed()) {
1828 return;
1829 }
1830
1831 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing standardized IceConnectionState "
1832 << standardized_ice_connection_state_ << " => " << new_state;
1833
1834 standardized_ice_connection_state_ = new_state;
1835 Observer()->OnStandardizedIceConnectionChange(new_state);
1836}
1837
1838void PeerConnection::SetConnectionState(
1839 PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState new_state) {
1840 if (connection_state_ == new_state)
1841 return;
1842 if (IsClosed())
1843 return;
1844 connection_state_ = new_state;
1845 Observer()->OnConnectionChange(new_state);
1846
1847 if (new_state == PeerConnectionState::kConnected && !was_ever_connected_) {
1848 was_ever_connected_ = true;
1849
1850 // The first connection state change to connected happens once per
1851 // connection which makes it a good point to report metrics.
1852 // Record bundle-policy from configuration. Done here from
1853 // connectionStateChange to limit to actually established connections.
1854 BundlePolicyUsage policy = kBundlePolicyUsageMax;
1855 switch (configuration_.bundle_policy) {
1856 case kBundlePolicyBalanced:
1857 policy = kBundlePolicyUsageBalanced;
1858 break;
1859 case kBundlePolicyMaxBundle:
1860 policy = kBundlePolicyUsageMaxBundle;
1861 break;
1862 case kBundlePolicyMaxCompat:
1863 policy = kBundlePolicyUsageMaxCompat;
1864 break;
1865 }
1866 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.BundlePolicy", policy,
1867 kBundlePolicyUsageMax);
1868
1869 // Record configured ice candidate pool size depending on the
1870 // BUNDLE policy. See
1871 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-pc/#dom-rtcconfiguration-icecandidatepoolsize
1872 // The ICE candidate pool size is an optimization and it may be desirable
1873 // to restrict the maximum size of the pre-gathered candidates.
1874 switch (configuration_.bundle_policy) {
1875 case kBundlePolicyBalanced:
1876 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR(
1877 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.CandidatePoolUsage.Balanced",
1878 configuration_.ice_candidate_pool_size, 0, 255, 256);
1879 break;
1880 case kBundlePolicyMaxBundle:
1881 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR(
1882 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.CandidatePoolUsage.MaxBundle",
1883 configuration_.ice_candidate_pool_size, 0, 255, 256);
1884 break;
1885 case kBundlePolicyMaxCompat:
1886 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_LINEAR(
1887 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.CandidatePoolUsage.MaxCompat",
1888 configuration_.ice_candidate_pool_size, 0, 255, 256);
1889 break;
1890 }
1891 }
1892}

1976PeerConnection::InitializePortAllocatorResult
1977PeerConnection::InitializePortAllocator_n(
1978 const cricket::ServerAddresses& stun_servers,
1979 const std::vector<cricket::RelayServerConfig>& turn_servers,
1980 const RTCConfiguration& configuration) {
1981 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
1982
1983 port_allocator_->Initialize();
1984 // To handle both internal and externally created port allocator, we will
1985 // enable BUNDLE here.
1986 int port_allocator_flags = port_allocator_->flags();
1987 port_allocator_flags |= cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_ENABLE_SHARED_SOCKET |
1988 cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_ENABLE_IPV6 |
1989 cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_ENABLE_IPV6_ON_WIFI;
1990 // If the disable-IPv6 flag was specified, we'll not override it
1991 // by experiment.
1992 if (configuration.disable_ipv6) {
1993 port_allocator_flags &= ~(cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_ENABLE_IPV6);
1994 } else if (absl::StartsWith(context_->trials().Lookup("WebRTC-IPv6Default"),
1995 "Disabled")) {
1996 port_allocator_flags &= ~(cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_ENABLE_IPV6);
1997 }
1998 if (configuration.disable_ipv6_on_wifi) {
1999 port_allocator_flags &= ~(cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_ENABLE_IPV6_ON_WIFI);
2000 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "IPv6 candidates on Wi-Fi are disabled.";
2001 }
2002
2003 if (configuration.tcp_candidate_policy == kTcpCandidatePolicyDisabled) {
2004 port_allocator_flags |= cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_DISABLE_TCP;
2005 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "TCP candidates are disabled.";
2006 }
2007
2008 if (configuration.candidate_network_policy ==
2009 kCandidateNetworkPolicyLowCost) {
2010 port_allocator_flags |= cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_DISABLE_COSTLY_NETWORKS;
2011 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Do not gather candidates on high-cost networks";
2012 }
2013
2014 if (configuration.disable_link_local_networks) {
2015 port_allocator_flags |= cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_DISABLE_LINK_LOCAL_NETWORKS;
2016 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Disable candidates on link-local network interfaces.";
2017 }
2018
2019 port_allocator_->set_flags(port_allocator_flags);
2020 // No step delay is used while allocating ports.
2021 port_allocator_->set_step_delay(cricket::kMinimumStepDelay);
2022 port_allocator_->SetCandidateFilter(
2023 ConvertIceTransportTypeToCandidateFilter(configuration.type));
2024 port_allocator_->set_max_ipv6_networks(configuration.max_ipv6_networks);
2025
2026 auto turn_servers_copy = turn_servers;
2027 for (auto& turn_server : turn_servers_copy) {
2028 turn_server.tls_cert_verifier = tls_cert_verifier_.get();
2029 }
2030 // Call this last since it may create pooled allocator sessions using the
2031 // properties set above.
2032 port_allocator_->SetConfiguration(
2033 stun_servers, std::move(turn_servers_copy),
2034 configuration.ice_candidate_pool_size,
2035 configuration.GetTurnPortPrunePolicy(), configuration.turn_customizer,
2036 configuration.stun_candidate_keepalive_interval);
2037
2038 InitializePortAllocatorResult res;
2039 res.enable_ipv6 = port_allocator_flags & cricket::PORTALLOCATOR_ENABLE_IPV6;
2040 return res;
2041}
2042
2043bool PeerConnection::ReconfigurePortAllocator_n(
2044 const cricket::ServerAddresses& stun_servers,
2045 const std::vector<cricket::RelayServerConfig>& turn_servers,
2046 IceTransportsType type,
2047 int candidate_pool_size,
2048 PortPrunePolicy turn_port_prune_policy,
2049 webrtc::TurnCustomizer* turn_customizer,
2050 absl::optional<int> stun_candidate_keepalive_interval,
2051 bool have_local_description) {
2052 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
2053 port_allocator_->SetCandidateFilter(
2054 ConvertIceTransportTypeToCandidateFilter(type));
2055 // According to JSEP, after setLocalDescription, changing the candidate pool
2056 // size is not allowed, and changing the set of ICE servers will not result
2057 // in new candidates being gathered.
2058 if (have_local_description) {
2059 port_allocator_->FreezeCandidatePool();
2060 }
2061 // Add the custom tls turn servers if they exist.
2062 auto turn_servers_copy = turn_servers;
2063 for (auto& turn_server : turn_servers_copy) {
2064 turn_server.tls_cert_verifier = tls_cert_verifier_.get();
2065 }
2066 // Call this last since it may create pooled allocator sessions using the
2067 // candidate filter set above.
2068 return port_allocator_->SetConfiguration(
2069 stun_servers, std::move(turn_servers_copy), candidate_pool_size,
2070 turn_port_prune_policy, turn_customizer,
2071 stun_candidate_keepalive_interval);
2072}

2244
2245void PeerConnection::OnTransportControllerConnectionState(
2246 cricket::IceConnectionState state) {
2247 switch (state) {
2248 case cricket::kIceConnectionConnecting:
2249 // If the current state is Connected or Completed, then there were
2250 // writable channels but now there are not, so the next state must
2251 // be Disconnected.
2252 // kIceConnectionConnecting is currently used as the default,
2253 // un-connected state by the TransportController, so its only use is
2254 // detecting disconnections.
2255 if (ice_connection_state_ ==
2256 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionConnected ||
2257 ice_connection_state_ ==
2258 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionCompleted) {
2259 SetIceConnectionState(
2260 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionDisconnected);
2261 }
2262 break;
2263 case cricket::kIceConnectionFailed:
2264 SetIceConnectionState(PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionFailed);
2265 break;
2266 case cricket::kIceConnectionConnected:
2267 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing to ICE connected state because "
2268 "all transports are writable.";
2269 SetIceConnectionState(PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionConnected);
2270 NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::ICE_STATE_CONNECTED);
2271 break;
2272 case cricket::kIceConnectionCompleted:
2273 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing to ICE completed state because "
2274 "all transports are complete.";
2275 if (ice_connection_state_ !=
2276 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionConnected) {
2277 // If jumping directly from "checking" to "connected",
2278 // signal "connected" first.
2279 SetIceConnectionState(PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionConnected);
2280 }
2281 SetIceConnectionState(PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionCompleted);
2282
2283 NoteUsageEvent(UsageEvent::ICE_STATE_CONNECTED);
2284 break;
2285 default:
2286 RTC_NOTREACHED();
2287 }
2288}

2290void PeerConnection::OnTransportControllerCandidatesGathered(
2291 const std::string& transport_name,
2292 const cricket::Candidates& candidates) {
2293 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/12427): Expect this to come in on the network thread
2294 // (not signaling as it currently does), handle appropriately.
2295 int sdp_mline_index;
2296 if (!GetLocalCandidateMediaIndex(transport_name, &sdp_mline_index)) {
2297 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)

2300 return;
2301 }
2302
2303 for (cricket::Candidates::const_iterator citer = candidates.begin();
2304 citer != candidates.end(); ++citer) {

2346// Returns the media index for a local ice candidate given the content name.
2347bool PeerConnection::GetLocalCandidateMediaIndex(
2348 const std::string& content_name,
2349 int* sdp_mline_index) {
2350 if (!local_description() || !sdp_mline_index) {
2351 return false;
2352 }
2353
2354 bool content_found = false;
2355 const ContentInfos& contents = local_description()->description()->contents();
2356 for (size_t index = 0; index < contents.size(); ++index) {
2357 if (contents[index].name == content_name) {
2358 *sdp_mline_index = static_cast<int>(index);
2359 content_found = true;
2360 break;
2361 }
2362 }
2363 return content_found;
2364}

2380bool PeerConnection::SetupDataChannelTransport_n(const std::string& mid) {
2381 DataChannelTransportInterface* transport =
2382 transport_controller_->GetDataChannelTransport(mid);
2383 if (!transport) {
2384 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
2385 << "Data channel transport is not available for data channels, mid="
2386 << mid;
2387 return false;
2388 }
2389 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Setting up data channel transport for mid=" << mid;
2390
2391 data_channel_controller_.set_data_channel_transport(transport);
2392 data_channel_controller_.SetupDataChannelTransport_n();
2393 sctp_mid_n_ = mid;
2394 cricket::DtlsTransportInternal* dtls_transport =
2395 transport_controller_->GetDtlsTransport(mid);
2396 if (dtls_transport) {
2397 signaling_thread()->PostTask(
2398 ToQueuedTask(signaling_thread_safety_.flag(),
2399 [this, name = dtls_transport->transport_name()] {
2400 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2401 sctp_transport_name_s_ = std::move(name);
2402 }));
2403 }
2404
2405 // Note: setting the data sink and checking initial state must be done last,
2406 // after setting up the data channel. Setting the data sink may trigger
2407 // callbacks to PeerConnection which require the transport to be completely
2408 // set up (eg. OnReadyToSend()).
2409 transport->SetDataSink(&data_channel_controller_);
2410 return true;
2411}

2425// Returns false if bundle is enabled and rtcp_mux is disabled.
2426bool PeerConnection::ValidateBundleSettings(
2427 const SessionDescription* desc,
2428 const std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>&
2429 bundle_groups_by_mid) {
2430 if (bundle_groups_by_mid.empty())
2431 return true;
2432
2433 const cricket::ContentInfos& contents = desc->contents();
2434 for (cricket::ContentInfos::const_iterator citer = contents.begin();
2435 citer != contents.end(); ++citer) {
2436 const cricket::ContentInfo* content = (&*citer);
2437 RTC_DCHECK(content != NULL);
2438 auto it = bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content->name);
2439 if (it != bundle_groups_by_mid.end() && !content->rejected &&
2440 content->type == MediaProtocolType::kRtp) {
2441 if (!HasRtcpMuxEnabled(content))
2442 return false;
2443 }
2444 }
2445 // RTCP-MUX is enabled in all the contents.
2446 return true;
2447}
2448
2449void PeerConnection::ReportSdpFormatReceived(
2450 const SessionDescriptionInterface& remote_description) {
2451 int num_audio_mlines = 0;
2452 int num_video_mlines = 0;
2453 int num_audio_tracks = 0;
2454 int num_video_tracks = 0;
2455 for (const ContentInfo& content :
2456 remote_description.description()->contents()) {
2457 cricket::MediaType media_type = content.media_description()->type();
2458 int num_tracks = std::max(
2459 1, static_cast<int>(content.media_description()->streams().size()));
2460 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
2461 num_audio_mlines += 1;
2462 num_audio_tracks += num_tracks;
2463 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
2464 num_video_mlines += 1;
2465 num_video_tracks += num_tracks;
2466 }
2467 }
2468 SdpFormatReceived format = kSdpFormatReceivedNoTracks;
2469 if (num_audio_mlines > 1 || num_video_mlines > 1) {
2470 format = kSdpFormatReceivedComplexUnifiedPlan;
2471 } else if (num_audio_tracks > 1 || num_video_tracks > 1) {
2472 format = kSdpFormatReceivedComplexPlanB;
2473 } else if (num_audio_tracks > 0 || num_video_tracks > 0) {
2474 format = kSdpFormatReceivedSimple;
2475 }
2476 switch (remote_description.GetType()) {
2477 case SdpType::kOffer:
2478 // Historically only offers were counted.
2479 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.SdpFormatReceived",
2480 format, kSdpFormatReceivedMax);
2481 break;
2482 case SdpType::kAnswer:
2483 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.SdpFormatReceivedAnswer",
2484 format, kSdpFormatReceivedMax);
2485 break;
2486 default:
2487 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Can not report SdpFormatReceived for "
2488 << SdpTypeToString(remote_description.GetType());
2489 break;
2490 }
2491}
2492
2493void PeerConnection::ReportSdpBundleUsage(
2494 const SessionDescriptionInterface& remote_description) {
2495 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2496
2497 bool using_bundle =
2498 remote_description.description()->HasGroup(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
2499 int num_audio_mlines = 0;
2500 int num_video_mlines = 0;
2501 int num_data_mlines = 0;
2502 for (const ContentInfo& content :
2503 remote_description.description()->contents()) {
2504 cricket::MediaType media_type = content.media_description()->type();
2505 if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
2506 num_audio_mlines += 1;
2507 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
2508 num_video_mlines += 1;
2509 } else if (media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA) {
2510 num_data_mlines += 1;
2511 }
2512 }
2513 bool simple = num_audio_mlines <= 1 && num_video_mlines <= 1;
2514 BundleUsage usage = kBundleUsageMax;
2515 if (num_audio_mlines == 0 && num_video_mlines == 0) {
2516 if (num_data_mlines > 0) {
2517 usage = using_bundle ? kBundleUsageBundleDatachannelOnly
2518 : kBundleUsageNoBundleDatachannelOnly;
2519 } else {
2520 usage = kBundleUsageEmpty;
2521 }
2522 } else if (configuration_.sdp_semantics == SdpSemantics::kPlanB) {
2523 // In plan-b, simple/complex usage will not show up in the number of
2524 // m-lines or BUNDLE.
2525 usage = using_bundle ? kBundleUsageBundlePlanB : kBundleUsageNoBundlePlanB;
2526 } else {
2527 if (simple) {
2528 usage =
2529 using_bundle ? kBundleUsageBundleSimple : kBundleUsageNoBundleSimple;
2530 } else {
2531 usage = using_bundle ? kBundleUsageBundleComplex
2532 : kBundleUsageNoBundleComplex;
2533 }
2534 }
2535 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.BundleUsage", usage,
2536 kBundleUsageMax);
2537}

2558// Asynchronously adds remote candidates on the network thread.
2559void PeerConnection::AddRemoteCandidate(const std::string& mid,
2560 const cricket::Candidate& candidate) {
2561 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2562
2563 network_thread()->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
2564 network_thread_safety_, [this, mid = mid, candidate = candidate] {
2565 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
2566 std::vector<cricket::Candidate> candidates = {candidate};
2567 RTCError error =
2568 transport_controller_->AddRemoteCandidates(mid, candidates);
2569 if (error.ok()) {
2570 signaling_thread()->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
2571 signaling_thread_safety_.flag(),
2572 [this, candidate = std::move(candidate)] {
2573 ReportRemoteIceCandidateAdded(candidate);
2574 // Candidates successfully submitted for checking.
2575 if (ice_connection_state() ==
2576 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionNew ||
2577 ice_connection_state() ==
2578 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionDisconnected) {
2579 // If state is New, then the session has just gotten its first
2580 // remote ICE candidates, so go to Checking. If state is
2581 // Disconnected, the session is re-using old candidates or
2582 // receiving additional ones, so go to Checking. If state is
2583 // Connected, stay Connected.
2584 // TODO(bemasc): If state is Connected, and the new candidates
2585 // are for a newly added transport, then the state actually
2586 // _should_ move to checking. Add a way to distinguish that
2587 // case.
2588 SetIceConnectionState(
2589 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionChecking);
2590 }
2591 // TODO(bemasc): If state is Completed, go back to Connected.
2592 }));
2593 } else {
2594 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << error.message();
2595 }
2596 }));
2597}

2642// Runs on network_thread().
2643void PeerConnection::ReportTransportStats() {
2644 rtc::Thread::ScopedDisallowBlockingCalls no_blocking_calls;
2645 std::map<std::string, std::set<cricket::MediaType>>
2646 media_types_by_transport_name;
2647 for (const auto& transceiver : rtp_manager()->transceivers()->UnsafeList()) {
2648 if (transceiver->internal()->channel()) {
2649 const std::string& transport_name =
2650 transceiver->internal()->channel()->transport_name();
2651 media_types_by_transport_name[transport_name].insert(
2652 transceiver->media_type());
2653 }
2654 }
2655
2656 if (sctp_mid_n_) {
2657 cricket::DtlsTransportInternal* dtls_transport =
2658 transport_controller_->GetDtlsTransport(*sctp_mid_n_);
2659 if (dtls_transport) {
2660 media_types_by_transport_name[dtls_transport->transport_name()].insert(
2661 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA);
2662 }
2663 }
2664
2665 for (const auto& entry : media_types_by_transport_name) {
2666 const std::string& transport_name = entry.first;
2667 const std::set<cricket::MediaType> media_types = entry.second;
2668 cricket::TransportStats stats;
2669 if (transport_controller_->GetStats(transport_name, &stats)) {
2670 ReportBestConnectionState(stats);
2671 ReportNegotiatedCiphers(dtls_enabled_, stats, media_types);
2672 }
2673 }
2674}
2675
2676// Walk through the ConnectionInfos to gather best connection usage
2677// for IPv4 and IPv6.
2678// static (no member state required)
2679void PeerConnection::ReportBestConnectionState(
2680 const cricket::TransportStats& stats) {
2681 for (const cricket::TransportChannelStats& channel_stats :
2682 stats.channel_stats) {
2683 for (const cricket::ConnectionInfo& connection_info :
2684 channel_stats.ice_transport_stats.connection_infos) {
2685 if (!connection_info.best_connection) {
2686 continue;
2687 }
2688
2689 const cricket::Candidate& local = connection_info.local_candidate;
2690 const cricket::Candidate& remote = connection_info.remote_candidate;
2691
2692 // Increment the counter for IceCandidatePairType.
2693 if (local.protocol() == cricket::TCP_PROTOCOL_NAME ||
2694 (local.type() == RELAY_PORT_TYPE &&
2695 local.relay_protocol() == cricket::TCP_PROTOCOL_NAME)) {
2696 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.CandidatePairType_TCP",
2697 GetIceCandidatePairCounter(local, remote),
2698 kIceCandidatePairMax);
2699 } else if (local.protocol() == cricket::UDP_PROTOCOL_NAME) {
2700 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.CandidatePairType_UDP",
2701 GetIceCandidatePairCounter(local, remote),
2702 kIceCandidatePairMax);
2703 } else {
2704 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
2705 }
2706
2707 // Increment the counter for IP type.
2708 if (local.address().family() == AF_INET) {
2709 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.IPMetrics",
2710 kBestConnections_IPv4,
2711 kPeerConnectionAddressFamilyCounter_Max);
2712 } else if (local.address().family() == AF_INET6) {
2713 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION("WebRTC.PeerConnection.IPMetrics",
2714 kBestConnections_IPv6,
2715 kPeerConnectionAddressFamilyCounter_Max);
2716 } else {
2717 RTC_CHECK(!local.address().hostname().empty() &&
2718 local.address().IsUnresolvedIP());
2719 }
2720
2721 return;
2722 }
2723 }
2724}
2725
2726// static
2727void PeerConnection::ReportNegotiatedCiphers(
2728 bool dtls_enabled,
2729 const cricket::TransportStats& stats,
2730 const std::set<cricket::MediaType>& media_types) {
2731 if (!dtls_enabled || stats.channel_stats.empty()) {
2732 return;
2733 }
2734
2735 int srtp_crypto_suite = stats.channel_stats[0].srtp_crypto_suite;
2736 int ssl_cipher_suite = stats.channel_stats[0].ssl_cipher_suite;
2737 if (srtp_crypto_suite == rtc::SRTP_INVALID_CRYPTO_SUITE &&
2738 ssl_cipher_suite == rtc::TLS_NULL_WITH_NULL_NULL) {
2739 return;
2740 }
2741
2742 if (srtp_crypto_suite != rtc::SRTP_INVALID_CRYPTO_SUITE) {
2743 for (cricket::MediaType media_type : media_types) {
2744 switch (media_type) {
2745 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2746 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION_SPARSE(
2747 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.SrtpCryptoSuite.Audio", srtp_crypto_suite,
2748 rtc::SRTP_CRYPTO_SUITE_MAX_VALUE);
2749 break;
2750 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
2751 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION_SPARSE(
2752 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.SrtpCryptoSuite.Video", srtp_crypto_suite,
2753 rtc::SRTP_CRYPTO_SUITE_MAX_VALUE);
2754 break;
2755 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
2756 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION_SPARSE(
2757 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.SrtpCryptoSuite.Data", srtp_crypto_suite,
2758 rtc::SRTP_CRYPTO_SUITE_MAX_VALUE);
2759 break;
2760 default:
2761 RTC_NOTREACHED();
2762 continue;
2763 }
2764 }
2765 }
2766
2767 if (ssl_cipher_suite != rtc::TLS_NULL_WITH_NULL_NULL) {
2768 for (cricket::MediaType media_type : media_types) {
2769 switch (media_type) {
2770 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2771 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION_SPARSE(
2772 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.SslCipherSuite.Audio", ssl_cipher_suite,
2773 rtc::SSL_CIPHER_SUITE_MAX_VALUE);
2774 break;
2775 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
2776 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION_SPARSE(
2777 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.SslCipherSuite.Video", ssl_cipher_suite,
2778 rtc::SSL_CIPHER_SUITE_MAX_VALUE);
2779 break;
2780 case cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
2781 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION_SPARSE(
2782 "WebRTC.PeerConnection.SslCipherSuite.Data", ssl_cipher_suite,
2783 rtc::SSL_CIPHER_SUITE_MAX_VALUE);
2784 break;
2785 default:
2786 RTC_NOTREACHED();
2787 continue;
2788 }
2789 }
2790 }
2791}

2793bool PeerConnection::OnTransportChanged(
2794 const std::string& mid,
2795 RtpTransportInternal* rtp_transport,
2796 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransport> dtls_transport,
2797 DataChannelTransportInterface* data_channel_transport) {
2798 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
2799 bool ret = true;
2800 auto base_channel = GetChannel(mid);
2801 if (base_channel) {
2802 ret = base_channel->SetRtpTransport(rtp_transport);
2803 }
2804
2805 if (mid == sctp_mid_n_) {
2806 data_channel_controller_.OnTransportChanged(data_channel_transport);
2807 if (dtls_transport) {
2808 signaling_thread()->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
2809 signaling_thread_safety_.flag(),
2810 [this, name = dtls_transport->internal()->transport_name()] {
2811 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(signaling_thread());
2812 sctp_transport_name_s_ = std::move(name);
2813 }));
2814 }
2815 }
2816
2817 return ret;
2818}

2873std::function<void(const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& packet,
2874 int64_t packet_time_us)>
2875PeerConnection::InitializeRtcpCallback() {
2876 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
2877 return [this, flag = worker_thread_safety_](
2878 const rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer& packet, int64_t packet_time_us) {
2879 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread());
2880 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): We should actually be delivering this call
2881 // directly to the Call class somehow directly on the network thread and not
2882 // incur this hop here. The DeliverPacket() method will eventually just have
2883 // to hop back over to the network thread.
2884 worker_thread()->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(flag, [this, packet,
2885 packet_time_us] {
2886 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread());
2887 call_->Receiver()->DeliverPacket(MediaType::ANY, packet, packet_time_us);
2888 }));
2889 };
